{
  "stem": "3964.1",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And our Jewish education, as such, as far as orthodoxy and so on is concerned, was perpetuated and, and very, very strongly [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] given, given an issue, where where all of us were exposed, even those children who had not been used for-- to, to orthodoxy from home were exposed to Judaism, not only Judaism but also Zionism, which was the first time I was exposed to it and came into the picture.",
      "word_count": 76
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, the groups which were formed were several Zionist groups, was Habonim and Agudat Yisrael.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And there were people who had come from Palestine, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] who were teaching courses in our school about settling of Palestine and, of course, the principles of, of Zionism.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they felt and, of course, the community felt the only place to be and go to have a better future for all of us was to go to Palestine and build, build a country for ourselves, where things which happened in Germany could not happen.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Things went, went along fine in Bad Nauheim obviously till 1938, November the 9th, 1938, during the Kristallnacht.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Unawares of what was going on politically-- after all, we were still children.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We're 12 and 13 years old.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "There were younger children there and older children there.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Around 10 o'clock on November the 9th, brown shirts and SS came through the school.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I, I still can see it in front of my eyes.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "They walked into the classroom where I was.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And that particular classroom held a Torah, the Sefer Torah, where we used to conduct our services.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "We had minyan every morning, a minyan being the village's services wearing tefillin.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "They took the Torah out of the ark and just tore it apart and officially declared school closed.",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
